reviews.reviewText: Very strong magnets and sturdy. I was a little nervous about the magnets coming off prior to purchasing, but they are perfect. My toddler adores these!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on February 1, 2024
reviews.reviewText: Bought as a Christmas gift. They come with a bag to carry them in. They are great quality and it’s easy to build with them.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2024
reviews.reviewText: The item is exactly as expected. My kids like playing with the magnetic pieces. The only downside is they are much smaller than I thought. Had I known they were this small, I would have not purchased this particular product.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 21, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Love these magnetic toys
reviews.reviewText: My kiddo loves these. Magnets are not as strong as the competitors but that is part of the reason kiddo likes them- the real magnatiles are too hard for him to pull apart. He loved building with these and then crushing the buildings. We’ve had our first set for over a year and they are like new - no magnets have fallen off or loosened. The storage bag they came in was cheap and we threw it away after a few uses but the toy id great. Just wish it came with more pieces. We have two sets now and still wish we had bought a third. Recommend these for 2-5 yrs old but with adult supervision ( because they do have magnets).

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 22, 2024
reviews.reviewText: My 3 year old has absolutely loved these!They came with a cute little green pull cord type bag which makes sitting them all together a game changer! Very good quality, and plenty of pieces to make different houses and things at one time! Def recommend!!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 14, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Not very strong magnets
reviews.reviewText: These were really cute and colorful. They stick to the fridge nicely but when it comes to building, they aren’t the strongest. But still pretty fun for the little kids 1-3 age range.

reviews.reviewTitle: Good starter gift for baby to develop brain
reviews.reviewText: TL;DRI think this is a good starter gift for my baby to develop his brain. I recommend this to babies and kids.My baby is more than 1 year old and starts to concentrate on playing toys which needs some thinking and understanding.So I bought this this for him and see if he likes playing these magnetic pieces. The results are satisfying.He loves these megnetic blocks and would like to sit there and play these blocks. I will wait a few days to see he loves these toys because he like build things or just because they are new.Pros:Not an expensive price for a starter set of magnetic toyscolorful, attract baby to play with it.quality seems adequate, but need to make sure baby not bite it.Cons:the strength of magnetic seems at the low bar. It is not strong enough to hold the structure unless there is support below the frame.
